Cape Town - Imizamo Yethu residents have accused the City of Cape Town of dragging its feet with regards to the provision of decent housing following a devastating fire in March.&nbsp; The residents of the Hout Bay informal settlement have been protesting since Saturday and blockaded roads and disrupted bus services.&nbsp; Four arrests have been made. Nearby property was also damaged and shots were fired outside a retirement village.&nbsp; Cape Argus